Author: karsa <wanghongtao114@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 3 12:37:03 2026 +0800

    fix: progress rings start at 12 o'clock instead of drifting with pct
    
    strokeDashoffset = 0.25 * circ was meant to shift the dash start to 12
    o'clock, but the dasharray pattern's period is dashLength + circ (depends
    on pct), so 0.25 * circ is not a clean fraction of the period. The
    visible start point therefore drifted around the circle for every
    different percentage — pct=10% started near 1 o'clock, pct=25% showed
    nothing at all (the gap swallowed the visible), pct=50% filled the left
    half, and pct=100% filled only 3/4 of the circle. Verified visually with
    a 7-percent sweep test SVG before applying.
    
    Replace the offset with transform="rotate(-90 cx cy)" on each progress
    circle, which rotates the entire element so the path start (3 o'clock)
    becomes 12 o'clock. Path direction is preserved, so the arc grows
    clockwise from 12 o'clock and the visible length matches pct exactly.
    
    Affects all three progress rings: calorie + burn in CaloriesTab, and
    phase progress in ChallengeTab.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>

